    "department": "Software",
    "description": "About Sesame\n\nSesame believes in a future where computers are lifelike - with the ability to see, hear, and collaborate with us in ways that feel natural and human. With this vision, we're designing a new kind of computer, focused on making voice agents part of our daily lives. Our team brings together founders from Oculus and Ubiquity6, alongside proven leaders from Meta, Google, and Apple, with deep expertise spanning hardware and software. Join us in shaping a future where computers truly come alive.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nWe're building a consumer hardware company where the brand is the product as much as the hardware is. Our web presence needs to reflect that: marketing site, product pages, commerce flows, campaign landing pages. The kind of work where the details, the motion, the type, the spacing, and the interactions are the product.\n\nWe're looking for a design engineer to own how all of that gets built. You'll work alongside a strong design, product, and marketing team who care deeply about craft.\n\nWe hope you'll also bring that same eye to some of our internal R\u0026D products. We're a research-heavy company, and the surfaces our product development team uses every day deserve the same craft as anything public-facing.\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES:\n\n - Build and ship our web presence.\n\n - Own the online commerce experience end-to-end, from browsing to checkout.\n\n - Translate design intent into production code that holds up to the mockup.\n\n - Build interactions, animations, and UI details that make the experience feel considered and intentional.\n\n - Work with designers and marketers to bring campaigns to life on the web.\n\n - Integrate with commerce platforms, CMS tools, and analytics/tracking infrastructure.\n\n - Infuse our internal R\u0026D product portfolio with design quality, usability, and product thinking.\n\n - Ship work that's fast, accessible, and works on every screen size.\n\n\nREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS:\n\n - Strong frontend engineering. You write clean, performant code and care about what browsers actually render.\n\n - Real design sensibility. You can look at a design mockup and know what's off, and you can improve a design in code without being told.\n\n - Experience with modern frontend frameworks (React, Next.js, or similar).\n\n - Headless CMS or headless commerce architectures.\n\n - A portfolio or body of work that shows range: visual craft, interactivity, technical ambition.\n\n - You've done this at a high level before, more than once, through the full lifecycle.\n\n - 5 or more years of relevant experience.\n\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:\n\n - You've brought design craft to every project you touch - external and internal.\n\n - Motion design or animation skills (CSS, WebGL, GSAP, Framer Motion, whatever your tool is).\n\n - Commerce experience: you've built the real thing with carts, checkout, and payment integrations.\n\n - SEO, page performance optimization, web analytics.\n\n - Familiarity with marketing workflows: how paid and organic campaigns land on the web, what matters for conversion.\n\n - You've worked somewhere where the website wasn't an afterthought.\n\n - Experience building and working with APIs.\n\n - Growth engineering instincts: funnels, attribution, and what happens after the click.\n\nSesame is committed to a workplace where everyone feels valued, respected, and empowered. We welcome all qualified applicants, embracing diversity in race, gender, identity, orientation, ability, and more. We provide reasonable accommodations for applicants with disabilities. Contact careers@sesame.com for assistance.\n\nFull-time Employee Benefits: \n\n - 401 (k) max employer match: 3.5% of compensation\n\n - 100% employer-paid health, vision, and dental benefits for you and your dependents\n\n - Unlimited PTO and sick time\n\n - Flexible spending account with employer matching up to $1,650/year (medical FSA)\n\n - Guardian Employee Assistance Program (EAP)\n\n - Opportunity to share in the company's success with competitive stock options\n\nBenefits do not apply to contingent/contract workers.",
